c: 48
v: 15
t: "The remaining behind, will say when/if you set out to (for) winnings/spoils of war to take/receive it: \"Leave us, we follow you.\" They want/intend that (E) they exchange/replace God`s speech , say: \"You will never/not follow us, as/like that God said from before.\" So they will say: \"But you envy us .\"But they were not understanding except little"